1
00:00:06,491 --> 00:00:08,201
Man, I sure miss Julie.

2
00:00:08,451 --> 00:00:10,662
Spanish midgets.

3
00:00:10,912 --> 00:00:14,457
Spanish midgets wrestling...

4
00:00:14,707 --> 00:00:18,878
Julie!
Okay, I see how you got there.

5
00:00:23,550 --> 00:00:26,302
You ever figure out
what that thing's for?

6
00:00:26,553 --> 00:00:28,430
I'm trying this screening thing.

7
00:00:28,680 --> 00:00:32,517
If I always answer the phone,
people will think I have no life.

8
00:00:32,767 --> 00:00:34,853
My God!
Rodrigo never gets pinned!

9
00:00:35,103 --> 00:00:37,564
<i>At the sound of the beep,
you know what to do.</i>

10
00:00:37,814 --> 00:00:39,691
<i>Hello. I'm looking for Bob.</i>

11
00:00:39,941 --> 00:00:41,151
<i>This is Jade.</i>

12
00:00:41,401 --> 00:00:45,321
<i>I don't know if you're still
at this number, but I was thinking...</i>

13
00:00:45,572 --> 00:00:48,867
<i>...about how great it was.
I know it's been three years...</i>

14
00:00:49,117 --> 00:00:51,453
<i>...but I was hoping
we could hook up again.</i>

15
00:00:51,703 --> 00:00:54,706
<i>I barely had the nerve
to make this call...</i>

16
00:00:54,956 --> 00:00:57,083
<i>...so you know what I did?</i>
- What?

17
00:00:57,333 --> 00:00:59,294
<i>I got a little drunk...</i>

18
00:00:59,544 --> 00:01:00,503
<i>...and naked.</i>

19
00:01:00,754 --> 00:01:03,548
Bob here!

20
00:01:04,424 --> 00:01:07,761
The One With Five Steaks and An Eggplant

21
00:01:52,580 --> 00:01:54,957
So what have you been up to?

22
00:01:55,207 --> 00:01:56,875
<i>Oh, you know, the usual.</i>

23
00:01:57,126 --> 00:01:59,086
<i>Teaching aerobics...</i>

24
00:01:59,336 --> 00:02:01,630
<i>...partying way too much.</i>

25
00:02:01,880 --> 00:02:03,549
<i>And in case you wondered...</i>

26
00:02:03,799 --> 00:02:09,263
<i>...those are my legs on
the new James Bond poster.</i>

27
00:02:10,806 --> 00:02:13,100
Can you hold on?
I have another call.

28
00:02:13,350 --> 00:02:16,270
- I love her!
- I know.

29
00:02:16,520 --> 00:02:19,356
- I'm back.
- <i>So are we gonna get together?</i>

30
00:02:19,607 --> 00:02:21,066
Absolutely.

31
00:02:21,317 --> 00:02:22,860
How about tomorrow afternoon?

32
00:02:23,110 --> 00:02:25,779
Do you know Central Perk?
Say, five-ish?

33
00:02:26,030 --> 00:02:29,700
<i>Great. I'll see you then.</i>

34
00:02:32,578 --> 00:02:36,332
Having a phone has finally paid off.

35
00:02:37,082 --> 00:02:39,335
You do a good Bob impression...

36
00:02:39,585 --> 00:02:41,253
...but when she
sees you tomorrow...

37
00:02:41,503 --> 00:02:43,934
...she's gonna realize
you're not Bob.

38
00:02:45,045 --> 00:02:47,639
Ah, you see Tatoo...

39
00:02:48,215 --> 00:02:52,015
Miss Jade's fantasy is to rekindle
the love she once had with Bob.

40
00:02:52,219 --> 00:02:56,280
You know what my fantasy is?
That you talk like a normal person.

41
00:02:56,758 --> 00:02:59,427
I'm hoping that when
Bob doesn't show up...

42
00:02:59,677 --> 00:03:03,556
...she'll seek comfort in the arms of
the stranger at the next table.

43
00:03:03,806 --> 00:03:07,644
Oh, my God.
You are pure evil.

44
00:03:07,894 --> 00:03:10,063
Okay, pure evil...

45
00:03:10,313 --> 00:03:13,441
...horny and alone.

46
00:03:14,901 --> 00:03:17,862
I've done this.

47
00:03:22,825 --> 00:03:25,370
Yeah, everybody's here.

48
00:03:25,620 --> 00:03:29,290
Hey, everybody!
Say hi to Julie in New Mexico!

49
00:03:29,541 --> 00:03:32,585
Hi, Julie.

50
00:03:33,002 --> 00:03:34,837
While Ross is on the phone...

51
00:03:35,088 --> 00:03:38,007
...everybody owes me
62 bucks for his birthday.

52
00:03:38,258 --> 00:03:43,054
Is there any chance that
you're rounding up from...

53
00:03:43,429 --> 00:03:44,222
...you know...

54
00:03:44,472 --> 00:03:46,891
...from like 20?

55
00:03:47,141 --> 00:03:50,019
Hey, we got the gift,
the concert and the cake.

56
00:03:50,270 --> 00:03:53,523
Do we need a cake?

57
00:03:53,648 --> 00:03:56,651
I know it's a little steep.

58
00:03:58,361 --> 00:04:01,072
But it's Ross.

59
00:04:01,322 --> 00:04:04,033
It's Ross.

60
00:04:04,325 --> 00:04:05,952
See you later.
I gotta go...

61
00:04:06,202 --> 00:04:08,997
...do a thing!

62
00:04:09,247 --> 00:04:11,374
Okay, sweetheart,
I'll call you later.

63
00:04:11,624 --> 00:04:14,294
You're not going
through with this, are you?

64
00:04:14,544 --> 00:04:18,298
You know, I think I might just.

65
00:04:19,215 --> 00:04:23,011
What are you guys
doing for dinner tonight?

66
00:04:23,261 --> 00:04:26,931
Well, I gotta start
saving up for Ross' birthday.

67
00:04:27,182 --> 00:04:30,143
I guess I'll just stay home
and eat dust bunnies.

68
00:04:30,393 --> 00:04:33,021
Can you believe
how much this costs?

69
00:04:33,271 --> 00:04:36,191
Do you guys ever
get the feeling that...

70
00:04:36,441 --> 00:04:38,151
...Chandler and those guys...

71
00:04:38,401 --> 00:04:42,739
...don't get that
we don't make that much money?

72
00:04:42,739 --> 00:04:45,533
They always say
let's go here, let's go there.

73
00:04:45,783 --> 00:04:48,912
Like we can afford to go
here and there.

74
00:04:49,162 --> 00:04:53,291
Yes, and we always have to go to,
you know, someplace nice.

75
00:04:53,541 --> 00:04:58,379
And we can't say anything about it,
because this is a birthday thing...

76
00:04:58,630 --> 00:04:59,964
...and it's "for Ross."

77
00:05:00,215 --> 00:05:03,218
For Ross.

78
00:05:04,385 --> 00:05:07,096
Oh, my God!

79
00:05:07,096 --> 00:05:08,807
I'm at work...

80
00:05:09,057 --> 00:05:12,894
...just an ordinary day,
chop, chop, sauté, sauté.

81
00:05:13,144 --> 00:05:16,231
Suddenly, Leon, the manager,
calls me into his office.

82
00:05:16,481 --> 00:05:19,442
They fired the lunch chef,
and guess who got the job?

83
00:05:19,692 --> 00:05:23,613
If it's not you,
this is a horrible story.

84
00:05:23,863 --> 00:05:25,907
Fortunately, it is me.

85
00:05:26,157 --> 00:05:28,576
And they made me head of purchasing,
thank you!

86
00:05:28,827 --> 00:05:30,703
That's so cool!

87
00:05:30,954 --> 00:05:33,832
Anyway, I think we
should go out and celebrate.

88
00:05:34,082 --> 00:05:37,502
You know, someplace nice.

89
00:05:41,631 --> 00:05:43,258
Someplace nice.

90
00:05:43,508 --> 00:05:47,595
How much you think
I can get for my kidney?

91
00:05:53,017 --> 00:05:55,228
You can't do this.

92
00:05:55,478 --> 00:05:58,773
I can't get a girl like that
with conventional methods.

93
00:05:59,023 --> 00:05:59,983
It doesn't matter.

94
00:06:00,233 --> 00:06:05,113
She wanted to call Bob. Bob could be
who she was meant to be with.

95
00:06:05,363 --> 00:06:08,241
You may be destroying
their chance for happiness.

96
00:06:08,491 --> 00:06:10,785
We don't know Bob.

97
00:06:11,035 --> 00:06:15,540
We know me. We like me.
Please let me be happy.

98
00:06:15,790 --> 00:06:19,627
Go over there
and tell that woman the truth.

99
00:06:19,878 --> 00:06:22,422
All right.

100
00:06:22,589 --> 00:06:24,966
Go.

101
00:06:34,601 --> 00:06:36,561
Listen, I have to...

102
00:06:36,811 --> 00:06:38,980
I have to confess something.

103
00:06:39,230 --> 00:06:41,608
Yes?

104
00:06:42,567 --> 00:06:45,695
Whoever stood you up is a jerk.

105
00:06:45,945 --> 00:06:49,574
- How did you...
- I don't know.

106
00:06:50,200 --> 00:06:55,997
I just had this weird sense.
But that's me, I'm weird and sensitive.

107
00:06:57,540 --> 00:06:59,584
Tissue?

108
00:06:59,834 --> 00:07:02,212
Thanks.

109
00:07:02,253 --> 00:07:04,547
No, you keep the pack.

110
00:07:04,798 --> 00:07:07,884
I'm all cried out today.

111
00:07:22,232 --> 00:07:25,610
Here is to my sister,
the newly appointed head lunch chef.

112
00:07:25,860 --> 00:07:27,779
Also in charge of purchasing.

113
00:07:28,029 --> 00:07:30,949
Head lunch chef,
also in charge of purchasing...

114
00:07:31,199 --> 00:07:34,911
Who has her own little desk
when Roland's not there.

115
00:07:35,161 --> 00:07:39,040
Lunch chef, purchasing, own little desk
when Roland's not there...

116
00:07:39,290 --> 00:07:43,920
...here's to my...
- Wait! And I got a beeper!

117
00:07:45,922 --> 00:07:47,841
That's fine, I'll just wait.

118
00:07:48,091 --> 00:07:50,552
Sorry.

119
00:07:51,136 --> 00:07:53,513
Monica!

120
00:07:55,056 --> 00:07:56,391
Are we ready to order?

121
00:07:56,641 --> 00:07:58,268
We haven't even looked yet.

122
00:07:58,518 --> 00:08:00,103
When you do, let me know.

123
00:08:00,353 --> 00:08:04,566
I'll be over there
on the edge of my seat.

124
00:08:08,695 --> 00:08:10,155
Look at these prices!

125
00:08:10,405 --> 00:08:13,908
Yeah, these are pretty "cha-ching."

126
00:08:14,159 --> 00:08:18,163
I know! What are these,
famous chickens?

127
00:08:18,413 --> 00:08:20,999
Sorry I'm late.
Congratulations, Mon.

128
00:08:21,249 --> 00:08:25,128
I'm not sorry I'm late. How incredible
was my afternoon with Jade?

129
00:08:25,378 --> 00:08:29,424
Pretty incredible, according to
the message on my machine.

130
00:08:29,674 --> 00:08:33,845
Why is this woman leaving a message
for you on my machine?

131
00:08:34,095 --> 00:08:35,972
I told her that
my number was yours...

132
00:08:36,222 --> 00:08:38,183
...because I couldn't
tell her it was mine...

133
00:08:38,433 --> 00:08:42,437
...because she thinks
my number is Bob's number.

134
00:08:42,687 --> 00:08:47,734
Tell me again.
What do I do when Mr. Roper calls?

135
00:08:47,817 --> 00:08:48,943
Do I dare ask?

136
00:08:49,194 --> 00:08:52,572
I'll start with the carpaccio,
and then the grilled prawns.

137
00:08:52,822 --> 00:08:54,532
Great, same for me.

138
00:08:54,783 --> 00:08:56,117
And for the gentleman?

139
00:08:56,368 --> 00:08:57,994
I'll have the Thai chicken pizza.

140
00:08:58,244 --> 00:09:01,331
But if I get it without
the nuts and leeks and stuff...

141
00:09:01,581 --> 00:09:03,500
...is it cheaper?

142
00:09:03,750 --> 00:09:07,504
You'd think, wouldn't you?

143
00:09:08,588 --> 00:09:11,966
I will have the side salad.

144
00:09:12,217 --> 00:09:15,178
And what would that
be on the side of?

145
00:09:15,428 --> 00:09:16,262
I don't know.

146
00:09:16,513 --> 00:09:21,059
Just put it right here
next to my water.

147
00:09:22,227 --> 00:09:24,104
And for you?

148
00:09:24,354 --> 00:09:30,068
I'm gonna have a cup
of the cucumber soup and...

149
00:09:31,695 --> 00:09:34,656
...take care.

150
00:09:35,991 --> 00:09:38,118
I will have the Cajun catfish.

151
00:09:38,368 --> 00:09:39,160
Anything else?

152
00:09:39,411 --> 00:09:43,999
Yes, how about a verse of
"Killing Me Softly"?

153
00:09:44,249 --> 00:09:48,420
You're gonna sneeze
in my fish, aren't you?

154
00:09:51,659 --> 00:09:54,564
Woah! Does anybody else feel like
they just gave birth to an alien?

155
00:09:54,829 --> 00:09:55,690
Yes.

156
00:09:56,641 --> 00:09:57,729
No.

157
00:09:58,190 --> 00:10:01,736
Plus tip, divided by six...

158
00:10:01,986 --> 00:10:05,615
Everyone owes 28 bucks.

159
00:10:05,698 --> 00:10:07,658
Everyone?

160
00:10:07,909 --> 00:10:10,244
Oh! You're right, I'm sorry.

161
00:10:10,494 --> 00:10:11,287
Thank you.

162
00:10:11,537 --> 00:10:15,416
It's Monica's big night.
She shouldn't pay.

163
00:10:15,666 --> 00:10:18,127
So five of us is...

164
00:10:18,377 --> 00:10:20,046
...33.50 a piece.

165
00:10:20,296 --> 00:10:23,758
No. No way.
Sorry, not gonna happen.

166
00:10:24,008 --> 00:10:27,386
Prom night flashback.

167
00:10:28,054 --> 00:10:30,806
Sorry, Monica.
I'm happy you got promoted...

168
00:10:31,057 --> 00:10:34,227
...but cold cucumber mush
for 30-something bucks?

169
00:10:34,477 --> 00:10:36,604
No!

170
00:10:36,854 --> 00:10:39,357
Rachel just had that little salad...

171
00:10:39,607 --> 00:10:43,236
...and Joey with his teeny pizza!

172
00:10:43,486 --> 00:10:45,404
Okay, Pheebs.

173
00:10:45,655 --> 00:10:48,324
How about we'll each
pay for what we had?

174
00:10:48,574 --> 00:10:49,825
It's no big deal.

175
00:10:50,076 --> 00:10:52,537
Not for you.

176
00:10:55,498 --> 00:10:57,792
All right, what's going on?

177
00:10:58,042 --> 00:11:00,127
I don't wanna get
into this right now.

178
00:11:00,378 --> 00:11:04,006
It'll make everybody uncomfortable.

179
00:11:05,049 --> 00:11:06,050
You can tell us.

180
00:11:06,300 --> 00:11:10,680
Yeah, hello? It's us.
We'll be fine.

181
00:11:16,894 --> 00:11:17,854
We three...

182
00:11:18,104 --> 00:11:20,314
...feel like that...

183
00:11:20,565 --> 00:11:25,528
...sometimes you guys don't get that...

184
00:11:31,409 --> 00:11:35,329
We don't have
as much money as you.

185
00:11:39,083 --> 00:11:40,543
I hear you.

186
00:11:40,793 --> 00:11:43,588
We can talk about that.

187
00:11:43,838 --> 00:11:46,632
Well, then...

188
00:11:46,841 --> 00:11:49,552
...let's.

189
00:11:51,762 --> 00:11:55,016
I guess I just never think
of money as an issue.

190
00:11:55,266 --> 00:11:58,936
- Because you have it.
- Good point!

191
00:11:59,770 --> 00:12:03,483
So how come you guys
haven't talked about this before?

192
00:12:03,733 --> 00:12:07,445
Because it's always something.
Like with Monica's new job...

193
00:12:07,695 --> 00:12:11,908
...or the whole Ross' birthday hoopla.

194
00:12:12,241 --> 00:12:16,746
I don't want my birthday to be
the source of any kind of negative...

195
00:12:16,996 --> 00:12:20,416
There's gonna be a hoopla?

196
00:12:21,459 --> 00:12:26,506
Basically there's the thing,
and then the stuff after the thing...

197
00:12:26,756 --> 00:12:29,634
If it makes anybody feel better,
forget the thing...

198
00:12:29,884 --> 00:12:31,886
...and we'll just do the gift.

199
00:12:32,136 --> 00:12:35,473
Gift? The thing's not the gift?

200
00:12:35,723 --> 00:12:38,518
No, we were gonna go see
Hootie and the Blowfish.

201
00:12:38,768 --> 00:12:40,186
Hootie and the...

202
00:12:40,436 --> 00:12:43,481
I can catch them on the radio.

203
00:12:43,731 --> 00:12:46,859
No. Now I feel bad.
You wanna go to the concert.

204
00:12:47,109 --> 00:12:49,487
No, look. It's my birthday...

205
00:12:49,737 --> 00:12:52,865
...and the important thing
is that we're all together.

206
00:12:53,116 --> 00:12:54,033
- All of us.
- Together.

207
00:12:54,283 --> 00:12:57,620
Not at the concert.

208
00:12:59,080 --> 00:13:01,541
Thank you.

209
00:13:07,505 --> 00:13:12,301
So, the Ebola virus.
That's gotta suck, huh?

210
00:13:16,455 --> 00:13:18,290
Gee, Monica.
What's in the bag?

211
00:13:18,541 --> 00:13:21,043
I don't know, Chandler.
Let's take a look.

212
00:13:21,293 --> 00:13:24,713
Oh, it's like a skit.

213
00:13:24,839 --> 00:13:27,591
Why, it's dinner for six.
Five steaks...

214
00:13:27,842 --> 00:13:31,679
...and an eggplant for Phoebe.

215
00:13:32,304 --> 00:13:36,141
We switched suppliers at work, and
they gave me the steaks as a thank-you.

216
00:13:36,392 --> 00:13:42,147
But wait, there's more.
Chandler, what is in that envelope?

217
00:13:42,565 --> 00:13:46,610
By the way, this didn't
seem so dorky out in the hall.

218
00:13:46,861 --> 00:13:51,323
Why, it's six tickets to
Hootie and the Blowfish!

219
00:13:52,908 --> 00:13:55,953
The Blowfish!

220
00:13:56,328 --> 00:13:58,956
It's on us. So don't worry.
This is...

221
00:13:59,206 --> 00:14:01,584
...our treat.

222
00:14:01,834 --> 00:14:04,295
Thank you.

223
00:14:05,921 --> 00:14:07,590
Could you be less enthused?

224
00:14:07,840 --> 00:14:10,259
Look, it's a nice gesture. It is.

225
00:14:10,509 --> 00:14:12,553
But it just feels like...

226
00:14:12,803 --> 00:14:14,305
Like?

227
00:14:14,555 --> 00:14:15,347
Charity.

228
00:14:15,598 --> 00:14:16,724
Charity?

229
00:14:16,974 --> 00:14:19,268
We're just trying
to do a nice thing here.

230
00:14:19,518 --> 00:14:23,606
But you have to understand, your
"nice thing" makes us feel about this big.

231
00:14:23,856 --> 00:14:28,319
Actually, it makes us feel that big.

232
00:14:29,820 --> 00:14:32,573
I don't understand.
We can't win with you guys.

233
00:14:32,823 --> 00:14:35,910
If you guys feel this big,
maybe that's not our fault.

234
00:14:36,160 --> 00:14:39,538
Maybe that's just how you feel.

235
00:14:40,915 --> 00:14:43,626
Now you're telling us how we feel.

236
00:14:43,876 --> 00:14:45,795
We never should have talked about this.

237
00:14:46,045 --> 00:14:48,172
I'm gonna pass on the concert.

238
00:14:48,422 --> 00:14:52,843
I'm just not in a very
"Hootie" place right now.

239
00:14:54,386 --> 00:14:56,305
- Me neither.
- Me too.

240
00:14:56,555 --> 00:14:58,599
Guys, we bought the tickets.

241
00:14:58,849 --> 00:15:03,437
Then you'll have extra seats
for all your tiaras and stuff.

242
00:15:03,687 --> 00:15:08,484
Why did you look at me
when you said that?

243
00:15:10,277 --> 00:15:12,071
So I guess now we can't go.

244
00:15:12,321 --> 00:15:17,409
Do what you want. Do we always
have to do everything together?

245
00:15:17,660 --> 00:15:19,662
You know what? You're right.

246
00:15:19,912 --> 00:15:23,332
Fine.

247
00:15:24,834 --> 00:15:26,794
All right.

248
00:15:27,044 --> 00:15:30,381
We're gonna go.

249
00:15:33,926 --> 00:15:38,389
It's not for another six hours.
We're gonna go then.

250
00:15:48,816 --> 00:15:50,025
Are you ready?

251
00:15:50,276 --> 00:15:55,197
Just let me grab my jacket
and tell you I had sex today.

252
00:15:55,823 --> 00:15:58,200
What? You had sex today?

253
